This paper focuses on optimizing network performance in information-centric networking architectures, specifically within the context of the Named Data Networking (NDN) architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses traffic engineering, caching strategies, and congestion control, which are all relevant to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
